value.value: A type of monocyte characterized by low expression of CCR2, low responsiveness to monocyte chemoattractant CCL2/MCP1, low phagocytic activity, and decrease size relative to classical monocytes, but increased co-stimulatory activity. May also play a role in tissue repair.

definition.value: Markers: CCR2-CX3CCR1+ (human, mouse, rat); human: CD16+, CCR5+, CD32/FcgRII-high, MHCII+, CD86+; mouse: CD62L-Ly6C-.

value.value: A splenic macrophage found in the white pulp of the spleen. Markers include F4/80-negative, CD68-positive, and macrosialin-positive.

definition.value: Markers: Mouse: F4/80-, CD68+, macrosialin+.

value.value: A splenic white pulp macrophage found in and around the germinal centers of the white pulp of the spleen that participates in phagocytosis of apoptotic B cells from the germinal centers. A marker for a cell of this type is Mertk-positive.
A tissue-resident macrophage found in the central nervous system.
A thymic macrophage found in the thymic medulla.
A thymic macrophage found in the thymic cortex.

A lymph node macrophage found in the subcapsular sinus of lymph nodes that participates in sensing, clearance, and antigen presentation of lymph-borne particulate antigens. This macrophage is capable of activating invaraint NKT cells and is CD169-positive.
A lymph node macrophage found in the cortex of lymph nodes, in particular in and around the germinal centers, and that participates in phagocytosis of apoptotic B cells from the germinal centers.
An elicited macrophage characterized by low production of pro-inflammatory and Th1 polarizing cytokines and high expression of arginase-1, and associated with tissue remodelling.

definition.value: Role or process: tissue remodeling.

value.value: An immature T cell located in the thymus.

label.value: naive thymus-derived CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell

value.value: An antigen inexperienced CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD127-positive and CD62L-positive. This cell type develops in the thymus. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD62L-high, and CD44-low.

definition.value: These cells have not been exposed to antigen following thymic T-cell selection; found in blood and secondary lymphoid organs. This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'naive CD4+ T cell', but includes additional markers known to be expressed on naive CD4+ T cells.

value.value: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has differentiated into a memory T cell.
Mature T cell not yet exposed to antigen with the phenotype CCR7-positive, CD45RA-positive, and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD62L-high and CD44-low.
CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype RORgamma-t-positive, CXCR3-negative, CCR6-positive, and capable of producing IL-17.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'Th17 CD4+ T cell', but its logical definition includes additional known characteristics of T-helper 17 T cells.

label.value: naive thymus-derived CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell

value.value: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has not experienced activation via antigen contact and has the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CCR7-positive and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD62L-high and CD44-low.

definition.value: This cell traffics in secondary lymphoid organs and blood.  This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'naive CD8+ T cell', but includes additional markers known to be expressed on naive CD8+ T cells.

label.value: effector memory CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell

value.value: CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'effector memory CD4+ T cell', but includes additional markers known to be expressed on effector memory CD4+ T cells.

value.value: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has differentiated into a memory T cell.
A mature T cell that differentiated and acquired cytotoxic function with the phenotype perforin-positive and granzyme-B positive.
A differentiated T cell with ability to traffic to peripheral tissues and is capable of mounting a specific immune response.

label.value: effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell

value.value: CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD127-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD45RO-positive, and CD25-negative.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'effector memory CD8+ T cell', but includes additional markers known to be expressed on effector memory CD8+ T cells.

value.value: An immature alpha-beta T-cell that express Egr2. These cells give rise to T cells expressing NK markers.

label.value: surface intraepithelial CD8+ alph alpha positive alpha/beta lymphocyte
surface intraepithelial CD8+ alpha alpha positive alpha/beta lymphocyte

value.value: An alpha-beta intraepithelial T cell with the phenotype CD8-alpha-alpha-positive located in the columnar epithelium of the gastrointestinal tract. These cells have a memory phenotype of CD2-negative and CD5-negative.

An alpha-beta T cell expressing NK cell markers that is CD1d restricted and expresses specific V-alpha chains. NK T cells of this type recognize the glycolipid alpha-galactosylceramide in the context of CD1d.

definition.value: In mouse the canonical TCR is V-alpha-14, and in humans it is V-alpha 24.

value.value: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has cytotoxic function.

label.value: CD4-negative, CD8-negative, alpha-beta intraepithelial T cell

value.value: A CD4-negative, CD8-negative, alpha-beta intraepithelial T cell that is found in the columnar epithelium of the gastrointestinal tract.

A lymphoid progenitor cell that is found in bone marrow, gives rise to B cells, T cells, natural killer cells and dendritic cells, and has the phenotype Lin-negative, Kit-positive, Sca-1-positive, FLT3-positive, CD34-positive, CD150 negative, and GlyA-negative.

definition.value: Markers are associated with mouse cells. ELP transcription factors include E2A-positive, Ikaros-positive, EBF-negative, Pax5-negative, PU.1-negative.

label.value: CD16-negative, CD56-bright natural killer cell, human

value.value: NK cell that has the phenotype CD56-bright, CD16-negative, and CD84-positive with the function to secrete interferon-gamma but is not cytotoxic.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'CD16-CD56bright NK cell'. Markers are associated with human cell types.

value.value: An alpha-beta T cell that is found in the lamina propria of mucosal tissues and is restricted by the MR-1 molecule.
A dendritic cell arising in thymus that has the phenotype CD11c-positive, CD11b-negative, and CD45RA-negative.

definition.value: In the mouse this cell expresses CD8-alpha-alpha.

value.value: A plasmacytoid dendritic cell developing in the thymus with phenotype CD11c-negative or low, CD45RA-positive, CD11b-negative, and CD123-positive.
A lymphocyte of B lineage with the commitment to express an immunoglobulin complex.

definition.value: Types of B lineage lymphocytes include B cells and antibody secreting cells (plasmablasts and plasma cells).  Lymphocytes of B cell lineage can be distinguished from those of T cell lineage by their lack of CD3e (as part of the T cell receptor complex).

value.value: A lymphocyte of B lineage that is devoted to secreting large amounts of immunoglobulin.
An unswitched memory B cell is a memory B cell that has the phenotype IgM-positive, IgD-positive, CD27-positive, CD138-negative, IgG-negative, IgE-negative, and IgA-negative.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'IgD+ memory B cell'. Per DSD: Unswitched memory B cells are also reportedly CD48-positive, CD84-positive, CD229-positive, and CD352-positive.

value.value: A class switched memory B cell is a memory B cell that has undergone Ig class switching and therefore is IgM-negative on the cell surface. These cells are CD27-positive and have either IgG, IgE, or IgA on the cell surface.

definition.value: Per DSD: Class switched memory B cells are also reportedly CD48-positive, CD229-positive, and CD352-positive.

value.value: An activated mature (naive or memory) B cell that is secreting immunoglobulin, typified by being CD27-positive, CD38-positive, CD138-negative.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'plasmablast'. Plasmablasts are also reportedly CD48-positive, CD63-positive, CD229-positive, CD270-positive, CD319-positive, CD352-positive, CD361-positive, and IgD-negative.

value.value: A cell of a hematopoietic lineage.
Conventional dendritic cell is a dendritic cell that is CD11c-high.

definition.value: Originally described in the dendritic cell ontology (DC_CL:0000003)(PMID:19243617) These cells are also CD20-negative, MHCII-positive.

value.value: Dermal dendritic cell is a conventional dendritic cell that is CD11b-positive, CD205-positive and CD8 alpha-negative.

definition.value: Originally described in the dendritic cell ontology (DC_CL:0000019)(PMID:19243617). These cells are also CD281-positive (TLR1), CD282-positive (TLR2), CD283-positive (TLR3), CD284-positive (TLR4), CD285-positive (TLR5), CD288-positive (TLR8), and CD289-positive (TLR9).

label.value: CD7-negative lymphoid progenitor OR granulocyte monocyte progenitor

definition.value: Originally described in the dendritic cell ontology (DC_CL:1110000)(PMID:19243617).

value.value: An excitatory granule cell with a soma located in the granular layer of cerebellar cortex. A mature cerebellar granule cell has short dendrites with a characteristic claw-like appearance and a long axon that ascends to the molecular layer where it bifurcates (except in non-teleost fish, where it does not bifurcate) and extends mediolaterally to form parallel fibers.

It has been noted in at least some mammalian species that granule cells are the most numerous cell type in the cerebellum and in the brain, with at least 99% of all cerebellar neurons being granule cells.
Granule cell that is part of the cerebral cortex.
Granule cell with a soma found in the hippocampus.
A connective tissue cell found in bone.
A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD45RA-positive.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'effector CD8+ T cell'.  The functional characteristics of this cell type currently undefined in CL, which affects its proper placement within the hierarchy.

label.value: CD4-positive, CXCR3-negative, CCR6-negative, alpha-beta T cell

value.value: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has the phenotype CXCR3-negative, CCR6-negative.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'non-Th1/Th17 CD4+ T cell'.  Cells of this phenotype may include T-helper 2 T cells and some naive CD4+ T cells.

value.value: A monocyte that expresses CD14 and is negative for the lineage markers CD3, CD19, and CD20.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'monocyte'. Note that while CD14 is considered a reliable marker for human monocytes, it is only expressed on approximately 85% of mouse monocytes.

value.value: An intermediate monocyte that is CD14-positive and with low amounts of CD16.

definition.value: Definition is valid for human intermediate monocytes.

value.value: A dendritic cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'dendritic cell'. The inclusion of HLA-DRA in the definition restricts this definition to human dendritic cells.

value.value: A plasmacytoid dendritic cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive, CD123-positive, and CD11c-negative.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'plasmacytoid dendritic cell'. The inclusion of HLA-DRA in the definition restricts this definition to human plasmacytoid dendritic cells.

value.value: A hematopoietic oligopotent progenitor cell that has the ability to differentiate into limited cell types but lacks lineage cell markers and self renewal capabilities. Cell lacks hematopoeitic lineage markers.
